# Part 1 — Ambition

---

## 1. Do you think you are an ambitious person?

Yes, I’d say I’m quite ambitious, especially when it comes to my studies and future career. As a computer science student, I have many long-term goals, such as improving my programming skills, studying artificial intelligence, and hopefully pursuing further education abroad one day. I think ambition is important because it gives people motivation and a clear sense of direction. Of course, I also understand that ambition should be realistic and supported by consistent effort.

### 中文翻译：

是的，我觉得自己是一个挺有抱负的人，尤其是在学习和未来职业方面。作为一名计算机专业学生，我有很多长期目标，比如提升编程能力、学习人工智能，以及希望未来有机会出国深造。我认为 ambition（抱负）很重要，因为它能给人动力和明确的方向。当然，我也明白抱负必须现实，并且需要持续努力去支撑。

---

## 2. What was your dream when you were a child?

When I was a child, my dream changed quite frequently. At one point I wanted to become an astronaut because I was fascinated by space and science-fiction movies. Later, I became interested in technology and computers, especially after I started learning programming in middle school. Since then, my dream has gradually shifted toward becoming an engineer or researcher in the field of artificial intelligence.

### 中文翻译：

小时候我的梦想变化挺大的。有一段时间我想成为宇航员，因为我特别喜欢太空和科幻电影。后来，我开始对科技和计算机产生兴趣，尤其是在中学接触编程之后。从那以后，我的梦想逐渐变成了成为人工智能领域的工程师或者研究人员。

---

## 3. What is your main ambition in life now?

At the moment, my biggest ambition is probably to build something meaningful in the field of AI and technology. I don’t just want a stable job; I hope my work can actually solve real-world problems or improve people’s lives in some way. For example, I’m very interested in intelligent systems and robotics, so I’d love to work on projects that combine AI with practical applications. At the same time, I also hope to keep learning and growing throughout my life.

### 中文翻译：

目前我最大的目标，可能是在人工智能和科技领域做出一些真正有意义的东西。我不只是想找一份稳定工作，我更希望自己的工作能够解决现实问题，或者在某种程度上改善人们的生活。比如，我对智能系统和机器人非常感兴趣，所以我很想参与那些将 AI 与实际应用结合的项目。同时，我也希望自己能一直保持学习和成长。

---

## 4. Are you the kind of person who never gives up on dreams?

I think so, although there are definitely moments when I feel frustrated or doubtful. In my opinion, achieving a dream usually takes a very long time, especially in competitive fields like technology or research. So persistence is probably more important than talent in many situations. Whenever I encounter setbacks, I try to treat them as learning experiences instead of reasons to quit. I believe that as long as someone keeps improving steadily, they’ll eventually get closer to their goals.

### 中文翻译：

我觉得自己算是这样的人，不过我当然也会有感到沮丧或者怀疑自己的时候。在我看来，实现梦想通常需要很长时间，尤其是在科技或者科研这种竞争激烈的领域。所以很多时候，坚持可能比天赋更重要。每当我遇到挫折时，我会尽量把它当作学习经验，而不是放弃的理由。我相信，只要持续进步，人最终会离自己的目标越来越近。
